  "instructions": "<p>The best way to hunt here is luring 5-8 creatures and using the diamond arrow rotation (diamond arrow &gt; exevo mas san&gt; diamond arrow &gt; great fireball rune &gt; repeat).&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üíñ Always heal with <em>exura gran san</em> and try to keep your mana full at all times (if you get out of mana you will probably die).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>‚öóÔ∏è The recommended supply is for a level 150. &nbsp;If you have a higher level you may require less supply.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üõ°Ô∏è Use a physical protection set (Zaoan Helmet, Prismatic Armor and Legs, Guardian Boots, and Enchanted Werewolf Amulet).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üï∏Ô∏è Avoid getting more than 4 exotic cave spiders at once if you are level 150. You can bring a might or prismatic ring to swap in if you see that you are going to lure more than 4 spiders (keep in mind that every time you unequip and equip a ring of blue plasma you will need to use a bullseye potion again).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT: you will need at least 2 vampirism and 2 void imbuements.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üí°Tips:</p>\n<p>You can sell used ring of blue plasmas to Fadil on Darashia. So keep an eye on the timer of the ring. When it reaches 1 minute, unequip it and equip a new one.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The first floor has a bigger spawn and is overall a better place to hunt than the second floor.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The second floor has some spiderwebs blocking the path and you will need a physical damage weapon to break it.</p>",
